stg.name: Error history record parameter start address
Error history records number parameter address
Sector type ("Reserved" key word is mandatory)
Error severity (from lowest to highest severity)
EEPROM range start-end addresses (hex, comma sep.), e.g. 0-10, 20-ff
XML - Start and end parameter address to treat arrays parameters as arrays

cfg_const.name: SW_VERSION_PLATFORM
cfg_const.desc: Platform version. If set to "NA", then value defined in makefile is used.

cfg_const.name: SW_VERSION_MAJOR
cfg_const.desc: Major version. If set to "NA", then value defined in makefile is used.

cfg_const.name: SW_VERSION_MINOR
cfg_const.desc: Minor version. If set to "NA", then value defined in makefile is used.

attrib.desc: Application software module in which the error is defined.

prm.name: BL_APP_DOWNLOAD_FLAG
prm.desc: App checksum saved after programming valid app. Used for detecting presence of valid app.

prm.name: BOOT_NODE_ID
prm.desc: Node-ID used by boot-loader. The actual valid range for KWP2000 Node-ID is 0x21 - 0x7D.

prm.name: APP_TO_BOOT_FLG
prm.desc: Indicates which 'Diagnostic Session' is started in boot-loader sw reset from application. Always use default value 0.

prm.name: NEW_BAUD_RATE_FRM_APP
prm.desc: Baud rate defined by start diagnostic cmd with specific baud rate performed in app. Always use default value 0.

prm.name: BOOT_TO_APP_FLG
prm.desc: Flag indicating that app should send positive response after stop diagnostic cmd received in boot-loader. Always use default value 0.

prm.name: SAF_UC_DNLD_COMPLTE_FLG
prm.desc: Flag set by special safety uC flashing app indicating that SuC has been flashed. Reset by bootloader while flashing new SuC flashing app. Always use default value 0.

prm.name: SW_RESET_CONNECTED_TOOL
prm.desc: Connected tool. 0 - FENDT, 1 - PLUS1, Default: 255 - no tool connected.

prm.name: SW_RESET_NODE_ID_OF_CONNECTED_TOOL
prm.desc: Flag indicating if first cmd received from connected tool was sw reset. Always use default value 0.

sector.name: DEVICE_ID
sector.desc: Component ID i.e. Product Code + Device Serial Number etc. info

prm.name: SD_SR_NUMBER13
prm.desc: Day digit 1 (Value in ASCII) 0x41 -> A (ASCII) -> Monday ... 0x45 -> E (ASCII) -> Friday

prm.name: SD_SR_NUMBER16
prm.desc: Serial/Batch No. digit 1 MSB (Value in ASCII)

prm.name: SD_SR_NUMBER19
prm.desc: Serial/Batch No. digit 4 LSB (Value in ASCII)

prm.name: SAFE_UC_BOOTLOADER_VER_1 [SAF_UC_BOOTLOADER_VER]
prm.desc: Safe uC bootloader controller type 0x31 - Series 5, 0x32 - PVX

prm.name: SAFE_UC_BOOTLOADER_VER_2
prm.desc: Safe uC bootloader version (X.YZ). Major digit (X). Value in ASCII.

prm.name: SAFE_UC_BOOTLOADER_VER_3
prm.desc: Safe uC bootloader version (X.YZ). Minor digit 1 (Y). Value in ASCII.

prm.name: SAFE_UC_BOOTLOADER_VER_4
prm.desc: Safe uC bootloader version (X.YZ). Minor digit 2 (Z). Value in ASCII.

prm.name: SAFE_UC_BOOT_CREATION_DATE_1 [SAF_UC_BOOT_CREATION_DATE]
prm.desc: Safe uC bootloader creation date -- DD (Hex)

prm.name: SAFE_UC_BOOT_CREATION_DATE_2
prm.desc: Safe uC bootloader creation date -- MM (Hex)

prm.name: SAFE_UC_BOOT_CREATION_DATE_3
prm.desc: Safe uC bootloader creation date -- YY (Hex)

prm.name: SAFE_UC_APP_VER_1 [SAF_UC_APP_VER]
prm.desc: 1 - S5, 2 - PXEB, 3 - Bootstrap (only BL), 4 - Bootstrap (BL + common function), 5 - PXEP, 6 - HWTSW

prm.name: SAFE_UC_APP_VER_2
prm.desc: Safe uC application version (X.YZ). Major digit (X). Value in ASCII.

prm.name: SAFE_UC_APP_VER_3
prm.desc: Safe uC application version (X.YZ). Minor digit 1 (Y). Value in ASCII.

prm.name: SAFE_UC_APP_VER_4
prm.desc: Safe uC application version (X.YZ). Minor digit 2 (Z). Value in ASCII.

prm.name: SAFE_UC_APP_CREATION_DATE_1 [SAF_UC_APP_CREATION_DATE]
prm.desc: Safe uC application creation date -- DD (Hex)

prm.name: SAFE_UC_APP_CREATION_DATE_2
prm.desc: Safe uC application creation date -- MM (Hex)

prm.name: SAFE_UC_APP_CREATION_DATE_3
prm.desc: Safe uC application creation date -- YY (Hex)

prm.name: VALVE_HW_ID
prm.desc: Valve hardware identification. 10 = PVX S1, 15 = PVX S1.5, 20 = PVX S2

sector.name: SAF_UC_DEV_ID
sector.desc: Safety Component ID i.e. Version Number Date

prm.name: CTR_CR
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the ratio of port B displacement area to port A displacement area, i.e. CR=port B area / port A area

prm.name: CTR_K_BACK_PRES_CONTROL
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Proportional Gain Backpressure Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the closed loop error of back-pressure; Scaled pressure error plus feed-forward branch form spool flow demand.

prm.name: CTR_K_DAMP_M_IN
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Gain for Active DAing by P-Spool.
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the differentiated pressure signal for meter-in flow; scaled pressure signal plus joystick flow demand form the Pspool flow demand.

prm.name: CTR_DAMP_IN_CUT_OFF_FREQ
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Cut-Off frequency for First order Differentiator in Meter In and Smart Metering Modes.
prm.ddesc: Parameter should correlate to the frequency of free pressure oscillation when metering into the cylinder, i.e. no damping applied.

prm.name: CTR_K_DAMP_M_OUT
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Gain for Active DAing by T-Spool.
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the differentiated pressure signal for meter-out flow; scaled pressure signal plus joystick flow demand form the Tspool flow demand.

prm.name: CTR_DAMP_OUT_CUT_OFF_FREQ
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Cut-Off frequency for First order Differentiator in Meter Out Mode.
prm.ddesc: Parameter should correlate to the frequency of free pressure oscillation when metering out of the cylinder, i.e. no damping applied.

prm.name: CTR_K_PRESS_A
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the closed loop error of port A pressure in mode 3 'Pressure control'; Scaled pressure error form spool flow demand.

prm.name: CTR_K_PRESS_B
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the closed loop error of port B pressure in mode 3 'Pressure control'; Scaled pressure error form spool flow demand.

prm.name: CTR_ANTICAV_PRESS_A
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Reference Pressure Anticavitation Control Port A.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired port pressure to avoid cavitation in the cylinder. Value reflects the line losses plus particular margin.

prm.name: CTR_METER_OUT_FLOW_PERC
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Additional Meter Out Flow.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the percentage portion which the meter-out flow has to deliver additionally to its. Percentage portion reflects the margin which avoids unintended pre-tension of the cylinder. Fx: A value of 10% means 10% more meter-out flow than initially required by the joystick input.

prm.name: CTR_ANTICAV_GAIN_A
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Proportional Gain Anticavitation Control Port A.
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the closed loop error of anti-cavitation feature in mode 'SmartMetering'; Scaled pressure error plus parameter 'CTR_METER_OUT_FLOW_PERC' form a scaling factor which increases the initial Pspool flow demand.

prm.name: CTR_ANTICAV_GAIN_B
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Proportional Gain Anticavitation Control Port B.
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the closed loop error of anti-cavitation feature in mode 'SmartMetering'; Scaled pressure error plus parameter 'CTR_METER_OUT_FLOW_PERC' form a scaling factor which increases the initial Pspool flow demand.

prm.name: CTR_LSA_LIMIT
prm.desc: Electronic LS Limit Parameter - Reference Pressure LS Limit Control
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired maximum load pressure when metering to the port A

prm.name: CTR_LSB_LIMIT
prm.desc: Electronic LS Limit Parameter - Reference Pressure LS Limit Control
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired maximum load pressure when metering to the port B

prm.name: CTR_P_SPL_RAMP_UP
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - Time P-Spool Fully Enabled.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired time the Pspool flow is fully recovered when pump pressure is more than 5bar above load pressure

prm.name: CTR_P_SPL_RAMP_DOWN
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - Time P-Spool Fully Disabled.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired time the Pspool flow is fully collapsed when pump pressure is less than 5bar above load pressure

prm.name: CTR_MINA_LIMIT
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - Reference Pressure Minimum Backpressure Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the minimum back-pressure in the meter-out flow on port A

prm.name: CTR_MINB_LIMIT
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - Reference Pressure Minimum Backpressure Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the minimum back-pressure in the meter-out flow on port B

prm.name: CTR_T_SPL_RAMP_UP
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - Time T-Spool Fully Enabled.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired time the Tspool flow is fully recovered when back-pressure is more than minimum pressure

prm.name: CTR_T_SPL_RAMP_DOWN
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - Time T-Spool Fully Disabled.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired time the Tspool flow is fully collpased when back-pressure is less than minimum pressure

prm.name: CTR_SPL_CTRL_KP
prm.desc: Spool Position Controller Parameter - Proportional Gain.
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the closed loop error of the spool position; Scaled position error contributes to the voice coil current signal.

prm.name: CTR_SPL_CTRL_KI
prm.desc: Spool Position Controller Parameter - Integral Gain.
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the integrated closed loop error of the spool position; Scaled integration signal contributes to the voice coil current signal.

prm.name: CTR_SPL_CTRL_KD
prm.desc: Spool Position Controller Parameter - Differential Gain.
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the differentiation of the closed loop error of the spool position; Scaled differentiation contributes to the voice coil current signal.

prm.name: CTR_SPL_CTRL_EINT
prm.desc: Spool Position Controller Parameter - Control Error Integration Range.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the integration range of the closed loop spool position error; An position error outside this range will not be integrated.

prm.name: OBSOLETE_CTR_SPL_CTRL_I_RANGE
prm.desc: Spool Position Controller Parameter - VC Current Range.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the voice coil range, the distance between minimum and maximum voice coil current.

prm.name: CTR_PA_POS
prm.desc: PXEB Logic Parameter - Reference Pressure Back-/Feedpressure Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired pressure in port A when the flow demand (joystick input) is positive, e.g. meter-in flow to port B.

prm.name: CTR_PA_NEG
prm.desc: PXEB Logic Parameter - Reference Pressure Back-/Feedpressure Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired pressure in port A when the flow demand (joystick input) is negative e.g. meter-in flow to port A.

prm.name: CTR_PB_POS
prm.desc: PXEB Logic Parameter - Reference Pressure Back-/Feedpressure Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired pressure in port B when the flow demand (joystick input) is positive, e.g. meter-in flow to port B.

prm.name: CTR_PB_NEG
prm.desc: PXEB Logic Parameter - Reference Pressure Back-/Feedpressure Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired pressure in port B when the flow demand (joystick input) is negative e.g. meter-in flow to port A.

prm.name: CTR_VALVE_VAR
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the valve type 1-PXBM 2-PXBH 360 3-PXBH 4-PXBH Regen

prm.name: PXEB_OP_MODE
prm.desc: PXEB Logic Parameter - PXEB operation mode.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the operation mode. (Valid Range: 0-15) 0-Disabled 1-Meter In 2-Meter Out 3-Pressure Control 11-Continous Regen 13-Load Detection Regen 15-Smart Metering

prm.name: ENABLE_SPOOL_MONITORING
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the Enable status of the spool monitoring. 255-Enabled

prm.name: DITHER_FREQUENCY
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the Dither frequency. Dither function superimposes high frequent oscillation to the voice coil current signal. Range: 0 - 10000 Other possible values: 666, 222, 111.

prm.name: DITHER_AMPLITUDE
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the Dither amplitude. Dither function superimposes high frequent oscillation to the voice coil current signal.

prm.name: PP_SIGNAL_LPF_COEFF_B07
prm.desc: Constants for 7th order filter applied on port pressure.
prm.ddesc: This filter is a non-recursive lowpass filter (type FIR) with 7th order. The default coefficients are designed for suppressing frequencies above 60 Hz. Parameter specifies coefficients b0/b7

prm.name: PP_SIGNAL_LPF_COEFF_B16
prm.desc: Constants for 7th order filter applied on port pressure.
prm.ddesc: This filter is a non-recursive lowpass filter (type FIR) with 7th order. The default coefficients are designed for suppressing frequencies above 60 Hz. Parameter specifies coefficients b1/b6

prm.name: PP_SIGNAL_LPF_COEFF_B25
prm.desc: Constants for 7th order filter applied on port pressure.
prm.ddesc: This filter is a non-recursive lowpass filter (type FIR) with 7th order. The default coefficients are designed for suppressing frequencies above 60 Hz. Parameter specifies coefficients b2/b5

prm.name: PP_SIGNAL_LPF_COEFF_B34
prm.desc: Constants for 7th order filter applied on port pressure.
prm.ddesc: This filter is a non-recursive lowpass filter (type FIR) with 7th order. The default coefficients are designed for suppressing frequencies above 60 Hz. Parameter specifies coefficients b3/b4

prm.name: CTR_Q_BS
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Flow Alitude BucketShake.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the Bucket shake amplitude. Function superimposes oscillation to the flow demand.

prm.name: CTR_F_BS
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the Bucket shake frequency. Function superimposes oscillation to the flow demand.

prm.name: REGEN_TRANS_PRESS
prm.desc: Control PXEB Regen Parameter - Reference Pressure for Metering Mode Transition.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the load pressure (port A) at which the flow control shall shift from regenerative to double acting flow control.

prm.name: REGEN_TRANS_TIME
prm.desc: Control PXEB Regen Parameter - Metering Mode Transition Time.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the transition time for the transition from regenerative to double acting flow control. The parameter value relates to 10lpm port flow demand. Fx: A value of 50 ms will lead to 500 ms transition time at 100 lpm flow demand.

prm.name: OPEN_SPOOL_CONTROL_OPTION
prm.desc: Open Spool in Neutral Control Option.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the control options of the Tspool when the flow setpoint signal is zero. 0 - Neutral Position 1 - Floating Position 5 - configureable relief flow from port A 6 - configureable relief flow from port B 7 - configureable relief flow from port A AND port B, priority parameter specifies which port flow is active at a time

prm.name: OPEN_SPOOL_OPTION7_PRIORITY
prm.desc: Open Spool in Neutral Control Priority.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the control priority when OPEN_SPOOL_CONTROL_OPTION=7 is selected. 1 - no priority, the highest relief flow demand is being controlled 2 - Priority to port A; when relief from port A is zero the port B relief flow is controlled 3 - Priority to port B; when relief from port B is zero, the port A relief flow is controlled

prm.name: CTR_LS_LIMIT_DELAY_A
prm.desc: Electronic LS Limit Parameter - LS Limit Delay Port A.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the time delay of the electronic LS pressure limit function when metering to port A. Increasing values stabilize the response on sudden pressure changes.

prm.name: CTR_LPA_LIMIT
prm.desc: Electronic Load Protection Parameter - Reference Pressure Load Protection Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the relief pressure (port A) for the electronic relief valve function. Recommended to set this value at least 10 bar above Lsa/b setting

prm.name: CTR_LPB_LIMIT
prm.desc: Electronic Load Protection Parameter - Reference Pressure Load Protection Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the relief pressure (port B) for the electronic relief valve function. Recommended to set this value at least 10 bar above Lsa/b setting

prm.name: CTR_LP_DELAY_A
prm.desc: Electronic Load Protection Parameter - Load Protection Valve Delay from port A.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the time delay of the electronic load protection function. Increasing values stabilize the response on sudden pressure changes.

prm.name: CTR_LP_CAP_10BAR_A
prm.desc: Electronic Load Protection Parameter - Load Protection Valve Capacity.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the relief flow when port A pressure is 1) 10bar above relief setting LPA or 2) is 20 bar above LSA setting

prm.name: CTR_LP_CAP_MAX_A
prm.desc: Electronic Load Protection Parameter - Maximum LP Valve Capacity.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the maximum relief flow from port A (flow saturation) for the electronic relief valve function

prm.name: CTR_CHK_VALVE_FUNC_DELAY
prm.desc: Spool Linearization - Check Valve Function Delay.
prm.ddesc: Parameter dpecifies the maximum relief flow (flow saturation) for the electronic relief valve function

prm.name: CTR_K_FEED_PRES_CONTROL
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Proportional Gain Feedpressure Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter scales the closed loop error of feed-pressure; Scaled pressure error plus feed-forward branch form spool flow demand.

prm.name: CTR_ANTICAV_PRESS_B
prm.desc: Control PXEB Parameter - Reference Pressure Anticavitation Control Port B.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired port pressure to avoid cavitation in the cylinder. Value reflects the line losses plus particular margin.

prm.name: CTR_LSA_LIMIT_REGEN
prm.desc: Electronic LS Limit Parameter - Reference Pressure LS Limit Control.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the desired maximum load pressure when metering to the port A in regenerative mode

prm.name: CTR_LP_DELAY_B
prm.desc: Electronic Load Protection Parameter - Load Protection Valve Delay from port B.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the time delay of the electronic load protection function. Increasing values stabilize the response on sudden pressure changes.

prm.name: CTR_LP_CAP_10BAR_B
prm.desc: Electronic Load Protection Parameter - Load Protection Valve Capacity Port B.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the relief flow when port B pressure is 1) 10bar above relief setting LPA or 2) is 20 bar above LSA setting

prm.name: CTR_LP_CAP_MAX_B
prm.desc: Electronic Load Protection Parameter - Maximum LP Valve Capacity Port B.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the maximum relief flow from port A (flow saturation) for the electronic relief valve function

prm.name: CTR_LS_LIMIT_DELAY_B
prm.desc: Electronic LS Limit Parameter - LS Limit Delay Port B.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the time delay of the electronic LS pressure limit function when metering to port B. Increasing values stabilize the response on sudden pressure changes.

prm.name: CTR_POST_REGEN_FLOW_SCALE
prm.desc: Control PXEB Regen Parameter - Port Flow Adjustment after Transition.

prm.name: CTR_DIFF_FILTER_FREQ
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the relief pressure (port A) for the electronic relief valve function. Recommended to set this value at least 10 bar above Lsa/b setting

sector.name: SAFETY_DATA
sector.desc: Monitoring related params, Safety Controller Config Params etc.

prm.name: SM_TEMPR_M40_ERR_TIME_OUT_MS [SM_TEMPR_M40_ERR_TIME_OUT_MS]
prm.desc: Spool Monitoring Time Out at Temperature -40 Deg C.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the TimeOut value for the spool monitoring at temperature -40 deg.

prm.name: SM_TEMPR_M10_ERR_TIME_OUT_MS
prm.desc: Spool Monitoring Time Out at Temperature -10 Deg C.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the TimeOut value for the spool monitoring at temperature -10 deg.

prm.name: SM_TEMPR_20_ERR_TIME_OUT_MS
prm.desc: Spool Monitoring Time Out at Temperature 20 Deg C.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the TimeOut value for the spool monitoring at temperature 20 deg.

prm.name: SM_TEMPR_70_ERR_TIME_OUT_MS
prm.desc: Spool Monitoring Time Out at Temperature 70 Deg C.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the TimeOut value for the spool monitoring at temperature 70 deg.

prm.name: CTR_LS_LIMIT_MARGIN_A
prm.desc: Electronic LS Limit Parameter - LS Limit Margin Port A.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the pressure range at which the electronic LS pressure limit starts to reduce the P-spool flow to port A. Increasing values stabilize the response of pressure limit function.

prm.name: CTR_LS_LIMIT_MARGIN_B
prm.desc: Electronic LS Limit Parameter - LS Limit Margin Port B.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the pressure range at which the electronic LS pressure limit starts to reduce the P-spool flow to port B. Increasing values stabilize the response of pressure limit function.

prm.name: EEPROM_CONFIGURATION
prm.desc: Flag indicating change in EEPROM. A5: App sets new sector CRCs, 0: App validates sector CRCs. Necessary to set to A5 when new parameters are created.

prm.name: VALVE_HW_ID_BACKUP
prm.desc: Backup value of valve hardware identification. Automatically set by the PVXB itself to value of VALVE_HW_ID. 10 = PVX S1, 15 = PVX S1.5, 20 = PVX S2
prm.ddesc:
Lubomir Milko: Backup HW valve ID is always backed-up in PVXP. This parameter is copied from PVXP backup into new spare PVXB during auto valve configuration and used by spare PVXB S2 to detect whether it replaces PVXB S1.5 and if yes, then certain control parameters are not overwritten during spare valve configuration.
The backup HW ID parameter does not need to be defined by the user, it is automatically set to the value of VALVE_HW_ID parameter.

prm.name: DEBUG_INFO_MSG_RATE
prm.desc: Rate of transmission for Debug info message. 0 - disable debug messages.

prm.name: ERROR_INFO_MSG_RATE
prm.desc: Rate of transmission for Error info message.

prm.name: TIME_OUT
prm.desc: Time Out for TimeGuarding on Setpoint Message.

sector.name: SPOOL_DATA_1
sector.desc: Spool related parameters and Look up tables

prm.name: SPLPOS_REGEN_START
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the metering edge position of the regenerative circuitry. Valve type 3 - P-gallery to port A. Valve type 4 - port B to port A

prm.name: SPLPOS_FLOAT_START
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the metering edge position of Float circuitry.

prm.name: SPLPOS_REGEN_FLOAT_POS
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - Spool Position for REGEN AND FLOAT mode.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the Pspool position for basic regenerative mode (not flow controlled) and the Tspool position for basic Float mode.

prm.name: P_SPL_A_DB_OBSOLETE
prm.desc: (NEW ADDRESS 2432) Spool Linearization Parameter - P Spool Deadband
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the metering edge position of P-gallery to port A

prm.name: P_SPL_B_DB_OBSOLETE
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - P Spool Deadband.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the metering edge position of P-gallery to port B

prm.name: T_SPL_A_DB_OBSOLETE
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - T Spool Deadband.
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the metering edge position of T-gallery to port A

prm.name: LVDT_PIN_LENGTH_USED_BCKP
prm.desc: LVDT transducer pin length used in PVXB. This parameter is backed up in PXEP and it is copied into the actuator replacement during auto valve configuration (not for full slice replacement).
prm.ddesc: Backup value of LVDT transducer pin length used in PVXB. LVDT_PIN_LENGTH_USED parameter is automatically copied to this parameter LVDT_PIN_LENGTH_USED_BCKP during each PVXB bootup.

prm.name: SPOOL_TYPE_PSPOOL
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the capacity of the spool. 1 - 45L 2 - 90L 3 - 180L

prm.name: NO_OF_VALID_ENTRIES_IN_KV_LUT
prm.desc: Spool Linearization Parameter - LookUp Table Breakpoint Number.
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the number of valid entries in KV look up table depending on Valve Type.

prm.name: P_SPL_KV_CHAR_X_1 [P_SPL_KV_CHAR_X]
prm.desc: KV Characteristics for P-Spool - X axis.
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the x-axis breakpoint for the Pspool

prm.name: P_SPL_KV_CHAR_Y_1 [P_SPL_KV_CHAR_Y]
prm.desc: KV Characteristics for P-Spool - Y axis.
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the y-axis breakpoint (setpoint spool position) for the Pspool

prm.name: T_SPL_KV_CHAR_X_1 [T_SPL_KV_CHAR_X]
prm.desc: KV Characteristics for T-Spool - X axis.
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the x-axis breakpoint for the Tspool

prm.name: T_SPL_KV_CHAR_Y_1 [T_SPL_KV_CHAR_Y]
prm.desc: KV Characteristics for T-Spool - Y axis.
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the y-axis breakpoint (set point spool position) for the Tspool

sector.name: SPOOL_DATA_2
sector.desc: Spool related parameters and Look up tables

prm.name: P_SPL_REGEN_KV_CHAR_X_1 [X_P_SPL_REGEN_KV_CHAR]
prm.desc: KV Characteristics for regen mode P-Spool - X axis.
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the x-axis breakpoint for the regenerative metering

prm.name: P_SPL_REGEN_KV_CHAR_Y_1 [Y_P_SPL_REGEN_KV_CHAR]
prm.desc: KV Characteristics for regen mode P-Spool - Y axis.
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the y-axis breakpoint (set point spool position) for the regenerative metering

prm.name: T_SPL_FLOAT_KV_CHAR_X_1 [X_T_SPL_FLOAT_KV_CHAR]
prm.desc: KV Characteristics for float mode T-Spool - X axis.
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the x-axis breakpoint for the float metering

prm.name: T_SPL_FLOAT_KV_CHAR_Y_1 [Y_T_SPL_FLOAT_KV_CHAR]
prm.desc: KV Characteristics for float mode T-Spool - Y axis.
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the y-axis breakpoint (set point spool position) for the float metering

sector.name: SPOOL_DATA_3
sector.desc: Spool related parameters and Look up tables

prm.name: LVDT_CALIBRATION_TABLE_SIZE
prm.ddesc: This parameter specifies the number of valid entries in the LVDT calibration table.

prm.name: P_SPLPOS_MAX_A_PORT_OBSOLETE
prm.desc: P-Spool Linearization - Maximum Metering P Spool Position port A. (relocated to spool data 4)
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the maximum metering Pspool position towards port A

prm.name: P_SPLPOS_MAX_B_PORT_OBSOLETE
prm.desc: P-Spool Linearization - Maximum Metering P Spool Position port B. (relocated to spool data 4)
prm.ddesc: Parameter specifies the maximum metering Pspool position towards port B

prm.name: T_SPLPOS_MAX_A_PORT_OBSOLETE

prj_cfg.file_gen_scripts:
""" Template filling module for PXEB APP project.
.. note: This script is relatively small, completely customized to one project and there are almost no expectations of future updates. The script is therefore written only with efficiency in mind (whole project configuration XML file read sequentially just once), but modularity, scalability, readability or other maintainability features are purposefuly disregarded (or simply: excuse the mess...). """
import inspect from typing import Optional, Dict, Any
__script_name__ = "PXEB APP template filling module" __version__ = "1.1.0" __author__ = "Lubomir Milko" __location__ = r""
IDL_FORCED_SECTOR_NAME = "DIAGN_DATA_3" IDL_PARAM_BASE_HEX_ADD = "80000000" IDL_ARRAY_PARAM_START_ADD = 1127 IDL_ARRAY_PARAM_END_ADD = 1303
SECTOR_KNOWN_TYPE_DICT = {"DontCare": "DONT_CARE", "Config": "CONFIGURATION_DATA", "Diag": "DIAGNOSTIC_DATA"} DATA_TYPE_SIZE_DICT = {"U8": 1, "S8": 1, "U16": 2, "S16": 2, "U32": 4, "S32": 4} ERR_SEVERITY_BITS_DICT = {"Info": 0, "Warning": 1, "Critical": 2, "Severe": 3}
UNKNOWN_DICT_VAL = "UNKNOWN"
class TemplateFiller(): def __init__(self, config_file_generator: "ConfigFileGenerator") -> None: self.cfg_file_gen = config_file_generator # Create templates. self.tmpl_bkg_h = self.cfg_file_gen.get_template("Bkg_pr_data.h") self.tmpl_bkg_c = self.cfg_file_gen.get_template("Bkg_pr_data.c") self.tmpl_idl = self.cfg_file_gen.get_template("PVX_PXEB.idl")
self.tmpl_err_h = self.cfg_file_gen.get_template("Err_pr_data.h") self.tmpl_err_c = self.cfg_file_gen.get_template("Err_pr_Severity_lvl.c")
def fill_sector_param_templates(self) -> None: # Create blocks located directy in templates. blk_sctrs_list = self.tmpl_bkg_h.code_block.get_subblock("SECTORS_LIST") blk_prms_in_sctrs_list = self.tmpl_bkg_h.code_block.get_subblock("PARAMS_IN_SECTORS_LIST") blk_sctrs_attrib = self.tmpl_bkg_h.code_block.get_subblock("SECTORS_ATTRIB") blk_prm_bytes_sum = self.tmpl_bkg_h.code_block.get_subblock("PARAM_BYTES_SUM") blk_ram_copy_sctr = self.tmpl_bkg_c.code_block.get_subblock("EERAM_COPY_SECTOR") blk_idl_prms_list = self.tmpl_idl.code_block.get_subblock("PARAM_LIST")
sctr_idx = 0 sctr_offset = 0 sctr_app_data_start_add = -1 node_sectors_list = self.cfg_file_gen.xml_config_root.findall("cfg_sectors/sector") for node_sector in node_sectors_list: sctr_name = node_sector.find("name").text sctr_type = SECTOR_KNOWN_TYPE_DICT.get(node_sector.find("type").text, UNKNOWN_DICT_VAL) sctr_start_add = -1 sctr_last_add = 0 arr_prm_len = 0 arr_start_add = 0 arr_name = "" arr_data_type = "" idl_prm_gen = False
if sctr_type != UNKNOWN_DICT_VAL: blk_prms_list = blk_prms_in_sctrs_list.get_subblock("PARAMS_LIST") if sctr_type != UNKNOWN_DICT_VAL or sctr_name == IDL_FORCED_SECTOR_NAME: idl_prm_gen = True
node_params_list = node_sector.findall("cfg_parameters/prm") for node_param in node_params_list: prm_add = int(node_param.find("add").text) prm_name = self.__get_xml_child_node_text(node_param, "name") prm_type = self.__get_xml_child_node_text(node_param, "type", "P") prm_data_type = self.__get_xml_child_node_text(node_param, "d_type")
#--- DEFINE ARRAY PARAMETERS AS A SINGLE ARRAY PARAMETER if prm_type == "A": arr_prm_len += 1 if idl_prm_gen and (not IDL_ARRAY_PARAM_START_ADD <= prm_add <= IDL_ARRAY_PARAM_END_ADD): self.__define_idl_param(blk_idl_prms_list, prm_add, prm_name, prm_data_type) elif arr_prm_len > 0: # End of array parameter detected. Define it. self.__define_param(blk_prms_list, sctr_last_add, arr_name, "AS", arr_data_type, arr_prm_len) if idl_prm_gen and (IDL_ARRAY_PARAM_START_ADD <= prm_add <= IDL_ARRAY_PARAM_END_ADD): self.__define_idl_param(blk_idl_prms_list, arr_start_add, arr_name, arr_data_type, arr_prm_len) sctr_last_add += DATA_TYPE_SIZE_DICT.get(arr_data_type, 1) * arr_prm_len arr_prm_len = 0

def __define_param(self, blk_params_list: Any, param_address: int, param_name: str, \ param_type: str, param_data_type: str, param_array_length: Optional[int] = 0) -> None: if param_type == "AS": hndl_type = "ARR_" create_hndl_type = "ARRAY" else: hndl_type = "" create_hndl_type = "PARAM"
if param_array_length > 0: add_and_size = str(param_address) + "," + str(param_array_length) else: add_and_size = str(param_address)
blk_params_list.set_variables("HANDLE_TYPE", hndl_type, "PARAM_NAME", param_name, \ "CREATE_HANDLE_TYPE", create_hndl_type, "DATA_TYPE", param_data_type, "PARAM_ADD", add_and_size) blk_params_list.clone()
def __define_idl_param(self, blk_params_list: Any, param_address: int, param_name: str, \ param_data_type: str, param_array_length: Optional[int] = 0) -> None: if param_array_length > 0: param_name = param_name + "[" + str(param_array_length) + "]" blk_params_list.set_variables("DATA_TYPE", param_data_type, "PARAM_NAME", param_name) hex_prm_add = hex(param_address).upper()[2: ] blk_params_list.set_variables("HEX_ADD", IDL_PARAM_BASE_HEX_ADD[: -len(hex_prm_add)] + hex_prm_add) blk_params_list.clone()
def __get_single_param_name(self, full_param_name: str, get_array_name: Optional[bool] = False) -> str: single_name = full_param_name if full_param_name.find("[") > 0: if get_array_name: single_name = full_param_name[full_param_name.find("[") + 1: full_param_name.rfind("]")] else: single_name = full_param_name[: full_param_name.find("[") - 1]
return single_name
@staticmethod def __get_xml_child_node_text(xml_parent_node: "etree.Element", child_node_name: str, implicit_value: Optional[str] = "") -> str: node_value = implicit_value child_node = xml_parent_node.find(child_node_name) if child_node is not None: node_value = child_node.text return node_value
